      "span_text": "Discussion ALCAPA is a rare congenital cardiac malformation in infancy (1 in 300,000 live births) [CITATION_1] that produces a coronary steal phenomenon and usually requires surgical treatment in infancy. It appears with features of myocardial ischemia or cardiac failure and may be mistaken for dilated cardiomyopathy [CITATION_2]"
